<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-07-17T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-07-17T06:00:00-05:00" n="252" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d252">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A16/36: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-07-17T12:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">July 17,
                                        1928—noon</hi>.</date><lb/>[Received 3:19
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>72. Circular C. F. A. 15, dated July 15, relating to private manufacture
                            just received.</p>
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“The Chairman of the Special Committee has the honor to inform the
                                members of the Committee that its second session will open at Geneva
                                on Monday, August 27, 1928, at 11 a.m. Provisional agenda: Drafting
                                of a single text for draft convention.”</p>
                        </quote>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>